<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2004-03-15</DATELINE><TITLE>Germs, governance, and global public health in the wake of SARS</TITLE><BODY>A revolution in the governance of global infectious disease threats is under way, accelerated by events triggered by the outbreak of SARS in 2003. This review article analyzes pre-SARS trends in the governance of infectious diseases, examines the impact of the SARS outbreak on these trends, and posits that germ governance is now a criterion of “good governance” in world affairs.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>